istatd
------------------------------------------
istatd is a daemon serving statistics to your iStat iPhone application from
Linux, Solaris & FreeBSD. istatd collects data such as CPU, memory, network
and disk usage and keeps the history. Once connecting from the iPhone and
entering the lock code this data will be sent to the iPhone and shown in fancy
graphs.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.7-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  libxml2-2.10.4-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libxml2-devel-2.10.4-2
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/tiwilliam/istatd

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/tiwilliam/istatd/archive/refs/tags/r0.5.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack istatd-0.5.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./istatd-0.5.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/istatd-0.5.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/istatd-0.5.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(istatd)
  /etc/istat.conf
  /usr/bin/istatd.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/istatd.README
  /usr/share/doc/istatd/AUTHORS.txt
  /usr/share/doc/istatd/CHANGELOG.txt
  /usr/share/doc/istatd/README.txt
  /usr/share/man/man1/istatd.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man5/istat.conf.5.gz

